description: Josue and Jefferson Perez, 13-year-old twins, were last seen at around 4:30pm on Sunday, 20 yards from the shore in waist-deep water near Galveston's Pleasure Pier. The pair cannot swim.

title: Mystery as $40MILLION Powerball win goes unclaimed - lottery office say there's a single winner
description: Australia is still waiting to meet its mystery millionaire, with the Perth-based winner of the $40m Powerball yet to collect their earnings.

title: Anthony Albanese's government comes under fire over franking credit tweaks
description: Mr Albanese had previously ruled out changes to superannuation and franking credits ahead of last year's Federal election.

title: Still no plans for Biden to visit East Palestine
description: The White House on Monday said there are still no plans for President Joe Biden to visit East Palestine, Ohio - even though he promised he would visit the site of the train derailment.

title: Sex and divorce? Brits are now as broad-minded as the Scandinavians on the topics, new survey shows
description: While Norwegians and Swedes are traditionally seen as less uptight, they are more likely than we are to frown upon one-night stands.

title: People are more eager to share news online than check if it is actually true, study finds
description: Researchers found that Facebook and Twitter users were often too distracted to check if their posts were accurate.

title: BBC scraps plans to film Attenborough, 96, handling chicks over fears he could catch BIRD FLU
description: He has based his television career on getting close to nature. And Sir David Attenborough was hoping his latest series would give him the chance to interact with fledgling seabirds.

title: UK areas that could be plunged underwater by 2100 amid sea level rise
description: Flood damage is expected to increase by more than 25 per cent if action is not taken to counter climate change and rising sea levels, according to a study led by the University of Bristol.
